    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1988 Porsche 911 Carrera is a superlative example of the G-Body platform, featuring the coveted Getrag G50 five-speed transaxle with updated Borg-Warner synchronizers for flawless shift gates. The 3.2-liter air-cooled flat-six is equipped with Bosch Motronic DME fuel injection, providing a smooth idle and robust torque curve; a recent leak-down test confirms exceptional cylinder compression. The suspension maintains factory geometry with original torsion bars and Bilstein dampers, ensuring the communicative steering feel these cars are known for. Staggered Fuchs alloy wheels are fitted with fresh N-rated tires, and the braking system features four-piston calipers with zero rotor lip. The exterior retains its original luster with no evidence of panel misalignment or paint thickness variance, while the cabin boasts impeccable leather upholstery and fully calibrated VDO instrumentation. A mechanically sorted, turn-key investment for the serious enthusiast.",
