      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six engine. This high-revving powerplant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable locking differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. This example is mechanically impeccable: the rear subframe has been structurally reinforced, and both the rod bearings and VANOS system have been proactively addressed. The chassis remains taut with zero bushing deflection, riding on factory-spec dampers that preserve the original handling geometry. The exterior retains its factory depth with no discernible imperfections, while the interior leather shows zero bolster wear. A comprehensive service dossier accompanies this turnkey analog icon.",
